<br>
Against the other classes, try practicing your running cast techniques.   Get in a corner, cast, move around as he tries to hit you, ending up back in the corner 4.5 secs later...repeat.  Commonly known yet often unused tactic.  AA casting quickness stacks with focus too..keep that in mind.  That is another skill you may want to consider. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvelaelsoulrender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Velael Soulrender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/14/02 10:31:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mmogamers.com/hate/ikonboard/avatars/joe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Channeling helps..</span><hr size=1> I'll actually probably get it at some point, just because I hate all the times you run/stop/cast and get the interupt message.<br>
